<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Learn DSA</title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    <%- include('../../partials/head') %>
  </head>
  <body>

    <div class="d-flex">
      <%- include('../../partials/sidebar') %>

      <main class="flex-fill p-4">
        <div class="text-center">
          <h3>In-Order Traversal</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="slide active">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # In-Order Traversal (Overview)

            In-order traversal is a way to visit all nodes in a binary tree.

            The order is:

            1. Visit left subtree  
            2. Visit current node  
            3. Visit right subtree  

            ####Left → Root → Right####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              Root-->Left;
              Root-->Right;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="slide">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Step-by-Step Process

            For each node:

            1. Recursively traverse the left child  
            2. Process (visit) the current node  
            3. Recursively traverse the right child  

            This continues until all nodes are visited.

            ####Traversal(node) = L → N → R####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A-->B;
              A-->C;
              B-->D;
              B-->E;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Example Tree

            Consider this binary tree:

            ####InOrder: Left → Root → Right####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A-->B;
              A-->C;
              B-->D;
              B-->E;
              C-->F;
              C-->G;
            /mermaid

            We start from the root (A), but always go left first.
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Traversal Walkthrough

            Steps:

            1. Go left from A → B → D  
            2. Visit D  
            3. Back to B, visit B  
            4. Visit E  
            5. Back to A, visit A  
            6. Traverse right subtree (C → F → G)

            ####Result: D → B → E → A → F → C → G####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              A-->B;
              A-->C;
              B-->D;
              B-->E;
              C-->F;
              C-->G;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <div class="slide"> 
          <div class="slide-content markdown"> 
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Key Properties

            - In-order traversal of a Binary Search Tree (BST) returns sorted values  
            - Uses recursion or a stack  
            - Time complexity: O(n)

            ####BST ⇒ Sorted Output####

            mermaid
            graph TD;
              4-->2;
              4-->6;
              2-->1;
              2-->3;
              6-->5;
              6-->7;
            /mermaid
            </script>
          </div> 
        </div>

        <!-- CONTROLS --> 
        <div class="nav-controls"> 
          <button class="btn btn-outline-dark me-2" id="prev">← Prev</button> 
          <button class="btn btn-outline-dark" id="next">Next →</button> 
        </div> 
        <div class="progress-container"> 
          <div class="progress-bar" id="progress"></div> 
        </div> 
        <div class="slide-counter"> 
          <span id="current">1</span>/<span id="total">1</span> 
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
  <script src="/javascripts/render-slides.js"></script>
</html>
